":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However it is higly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for textual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This utility helps to define wether a set of contrast ratio matches AA and AAA or not.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"See for example ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/system.design.orange.com\/0c1af118d\/p\/2531b9-accessibility-compliance","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations\/OUDSWCAG21Ratio","url":"\/documentation\/oudsfoundations\/oudswcag21ratio"},"doc://OUDSFoundations/documentation/OUDSFoundations/PSFNMK":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"PostScriptFontNamesMapKey in shorter","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations\/PSFNMK","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PSFNMK"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudsfoundations\/psfnmk","title":"PSFNMK","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PSFNMK"}]},"doc://OUDSFoundations/documentation/OUDSFoundatio